article.headline: Miami 70, S.C.-Upstate 41
article.story: CORAL GABLES, Fla. -- Dwayne Collins scored 17 points as Miami remained unbeaten in a 70-41 rout over South Carolina-Upstate on Saturday. Miami outscored the Spartans 20-4 and broke the game open during a 7:51 span midway through the first half. Collins scored six points during the spurt and Julian Gamble's field goal with 6:45 remaining capped the run for a 25-11 Hurricanes' lead. Cyrus McGowan's jumper with 3:13 left in the half gave the Hurricanes their first 20-point lead at 33-13. Reggie Johnson finished with 13 points for the Hurricanes (7-0). Nick Schneiders led the Spartans (0-5) with 11 points. Mezie Uzochukwu's reverse layup 1:19 into the second half put South Carolina-Upstate within 14 points. But Collins responded with seven straight points in the next 2:33 to give Miami a 45-24 lead.
